page.title: 08Butterflies etc......
page.content: Many types of Butterflies are found.Common Blue,Small Copper,Small Heath,Graying,Gatekeeper,Meadow Brown, Green-Veined White and Small Tortoise Shell are amongst the varieties. Near the railway line Danish Scurvy grass and Early Forget-me-not grow in spring.There are about 200 species of wild plants growing on the Reserve. We found a lot of Cinnabar moth caterpillars feeding on Ragwort in July. On a hot sunny day Common Lizards can be seen basking in the sun.Snails of many kinds live on the Reserve,and moths,five types of bee,and Ladybirds climb the stems of the plants.
